The paper proposes a new technology for interactive video synthesis, which involves segmenting and reusing video elements. This involves computer vision techniques for loop-finding and compositing, which suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the user interface and human-in-the-loop aspects of the system, which could fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques for video synthesis, which could also place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
